{
  "stem": "10572.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They killed him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Martin Zimmer, who was the SS man who was in charge of those individual cells, took care of people like that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And Margie and I, many, many years later in 1974, Margie and I went back to Buchenwald with a friend of mine.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And there is today, in the cell, there is a chapel with a huge cross in memory of Pastor Schneider, who was killed at the moment when I was ready to return to freedom.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A little bit less than three months.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And the-- again, the unbelievable thing is that the only reason I was released from Buchenwald because of Mrs.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hamilton's affidavits had arrived in the meantime.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I would not have been released.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And again, one of the-- one of the cannibal kind of attitude, when my sister went to the Gestapo with the affidavits to show them that I had-- the Gestapo agent told my sister that they had a case against me for [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] was racial-- a racial crime, a relationship with a Gentile.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my sister was in shock.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he said, well, I'm not quite sure about it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This was on a Friday or on Saturday.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Come back Monday, and I'll check it out in the meantime.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So Edith lived with us over the weekend, couldn't tell my mother and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And she went back on Monday, and he said, no, he made a mistake, that he was ready to be released.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, my father was released much, much earlier, weeks earlier, because the head of the Gestapo in Hildesheim, Dr.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mercantaler, had it in for him, at least he thought.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He didn't know the big favor that he did my father.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he returned-- he ordered his return.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was put in jail.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the jail was just a couple of blocks from where we lived in a beautiful park.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he was put in this jail.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And his secretary would come with papers to sign, for him to sign, at the orders of Dr.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Mercantaler.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she would come to jail, and he would be taken out of his cell and had to sign those papers.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And while Mrs.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Pallenbaum, who was my father's secretary for many, many years, he told her when they were alone that there was-- he could see people walk along the walls of this park by looking through the window there.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They couldn't see him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But my father asked her to ask my mother to come at 1 o'clock in the afternoon and walk there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [CRYING]",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was-- the-- the situation in Buchenwald is-- is really beyond description.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It is-- much has been written about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "None has gotten close to it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It is hell.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Couldn't be worse.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was-- you know, every moment, the-- the-- the constant fear-- every moment you ran into an SS officer and he didn't like your face, that could have been your end, you know.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He would call you over and provoke you, and something happened, and he would kill you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My-- my cousin Walter was hit by an SS man because he looked too Gentile.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He looked too Aryan.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So there was no way.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no rationale.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was no way for you to anticipate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was no way of saying, if I do this, I am out of danger.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Could have been just the opposite.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] By the way, the men who were-- the kapo, Walter, who beat me, the [NON-ENGLISH], about six months after, he was killed by his own kapo buddies.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So there's this peculiar sense of criminal justice that-- [PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] So then when I got back--",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When your father was released.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, so my father was one day-- was taken over to the Gestapo headquarters to be interrogated by Dr.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mercantaler And Mercantaler told him that he wanted to have him sell his house to this-and-this man.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father said to him, no, he wouldn't.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father-- that was his house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he would sell it to our next door neighbor, Dr.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Claudets.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Mercantaler said to him, you know, I can get you-- I can keep you in jail.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father looked at him and he said, Dr.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Mercantaler, after Buchenwald, there is nothing-- nothing you can threaten me with.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Mercantaler somehow told him at the end of these interrogations that you and I-- saying to my father-- have crossed swords with great bravery, somehow respecting.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one of the nice things that happened after I got out of service, there was an article in the newspaper, British intelligence looking for evidence that Dr.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Mercantaler had been member of the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
